HDR Video
-----------
#video#hdr#hdr10#hlg#dobly

HDR - High dynamic range


Formats
-------
HDR10
    - CTA (Consumer Technology Association) / CES
    - 2015
    - Free Royality
    - PQ
    - 10 bit
    - Peak Luminance / 10,000 nits / Contents 1,000~4,000 nits
    - Color primaries / Rec.2020 / Contents DCI-P3
    - Static Metadata
    - Backward compatibility : None
    - PQ10 format is same as HDR10 without the metadata


Dolby Vision
    - Dolby
    - 2014
    - Proprietary
    - PQ (in most profilies) / SDR (in profiles 4, 8.2, 9) / HLG (in profile 8.4)
    - 10 bit or 12 bit
    - Peak Luminance / 10,000 nits / Cntents at least 1,000, 4,000 nits common
    - Color primaries / Rec.2020 / Contents as least DCI-P3
    - Static Metadata / Dynamic (Automaticaly generated, Manually generated trims)
    - Dependent on profile / None / SDR / HDR10 / HLG / UHD Blu-ray
    - all profiles suppot the same Dolby Vision dynamic metadata

HDR10+
    - Samsung
    - 2017
    - Free (for content company), Yearly license (for manufacturer)
    - PQ
    - 10 bit (or more)
    - Peak Luminance / 10,000 nits / Contents 1,000 ~ 4,000 nits
    - Color primaries / Rec.2020 / Contents DCI-P3
    - Static Metadata / Dynamic (Manually generated trims)
    - Backwark compatibility : HDR10

HLG10
    - NHK and BBC
    - 2015
    - Free Royality
    - HLG
    - 10 bit
    - Peak luminance / variable / Contents 1,000 nits common
    - Color primaries / Rec.2020 / Contents DCI-P3
    - Metadata: None
    - Backward compatibility: SDR displays supporting Rec.2020 (such as UHD-TV)

SDR
    - Maximum luminance level of arround 100 nits
    - Rec.709/sRGB gamut



* Transfer function
    - Linear    / sRGB and Rec.709
    - Gamma     / Rec.601, Rec.709, Rec.2020
    - Logarithmic
    - HDR       / PQ (Perceptual quantizer) - Rec.2100 / HLG

* Color primary
    - Color space
    - Gamut / Ghromaticity space

* nits
    = cd/m^2   / candela per sqare metre
    - The unit is based on the candelar, the SI unit of luminous intensity

* What difference between Rec.2100 and Rec.2020
    - Rec.2100 define HDR
    - Rec.2020 define only color sapce
    - Rec.2100 = Rec.2020 + HDR

* What difference between HDR and Chromaticity
